description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a Band 7 Clinical Trial Start-up Specialist Research Nurse to join the research team at the Whittington Health NHS Trust to support the delivery of high quality research. You will be responsible for the clinical aspect of setting up new studies, study initiation and the research care pathway design. You will also be responsible for clinical supervision of research nurses up to Band 6 and share line management with the Research Team Lead. This will involve promoting and embedding a research culture within the Trust, acting as a resource to patients and multi-professional colleagues and building effective working relations with other local staff &amp; departments. The successful candidate will be a valuable member of the research team who manage and support clinical trials.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supporting research at the Whittington Health NHS Trust, with a particular emphasis on ensuring that commercial clinical trials are costed, set-up and delivered in line with NIHR HLOs (high level objectives) and contractual arrangements is a priority. You will monitor these processes, implement change where necessary and maintain high standards at all times. You should be able to demonstrate enthusiasm and innovation when faced with challenges and will utilise management skills in conducting the trials and managing their caseload. Your clinical experience and training will allow you to contribute to the presentation of trials to potential participants to ensure their appropriate recruitment, treatment and retention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKayleigh GilbertJob titleResearch Team LeadEmail addresskayleigh.gilbert@nhs.netTelephone number020 7288 3585&lt;/p&gt;
